                  <tr>
                    <td>EQ does have a limited macro capability.  You have 100 available 5 line spots to write a macro in.  These are most useful for doing custom emotes: i.e. Meechai rubs noses with (target)&quot;, or &quot;Meechai backs up to the corpse and marks it as his own&quot;.  They are also used to do several tasks with one keystroke, like forage, detect traps and disarm traps.  This is useful for skill practicing, but once you launch it, your stuck until the macro finishes.  THIS IS THE MAIN REASON MACROS ARE A BAD IDEA ...</td>
