                    <td class="forumAlternate" >Filo,

In your Everquest directory there is a sub-directory called MAPS.  I created a sub-directory under that one, called it SAVEMAPS, and copied all the existing map files into it.  (I'm a yellow-bellied coward (and fiercly PROUD of it :) ) and I don't like to do things I can't undo.)  You then unzip the EQ-Maps files into the MAPS directory, overwriting the existing files, and off you go.  If you decide you don't like the new maps  :?:  just copy the old ones back into the MAPS directory ...</td>
