                  <tr>
                    <td>The macro that seems to work best is this:

/stopsong

/cast xx

It has been discussed several other places on the board, but the problem with putting the pause command in a macro is that you have to wait out the timer if you miss a note.  With this macro, you only have to hit the key once, not twice as you do when you just drag the gem to the hot key.  When you miss a note, simply hit the hot key again and you're off.

For instrument swapping, I use a hotkey window that I picked up ...</td>
